('29b6b449-9802-47fb-b4be-8cd7216a4942','225c6acb-ad7d-4e4d-bf3f-fd47447f7eaf',NULL,1,1,'Mount Bracket','Mount the bracket in the pictured location using the supplied fixings.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/732a5b5b-6e80-4825-8a80-f997df590c79/step_02.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('bad0a51c-d4ab-4cb3-81f3-806d94afcfaa','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,3,3,'Access Panel','Pop out the panel indicated, and pull it down partially.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_03.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('1eb0efb5-7f54-44ab-a443-84489f35ba53','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,4,4,'Remove Side Panel and A/C Vent','Remove the side panel and A/C vent surround as pictured. Pieces can be removed by firmly pulling to release the clips.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_04.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('3b049da1-af15-468e-bee6-5eba4a1e8302','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,5,5,'Remove Dash Cluster Surround','Remove the dash cluster surround. Lower the steering wheel to allow it to be slid out of the way. Remove the four screws that hold the cluster in place.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_05.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('ea9d2fa7-4ebc-4bb2-a32b-fc997bfe4b39','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,6,6,'Access Wiring Loom','Pull the cluster forward to gain access to the wiring loom. Locate the main white plug closest to the side of the cluster.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_06.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('67694327-cb35-4d79-ae66-083b2ac93bcd','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,7,7,'Locate and Unclip Wires','Locate the wires indicated. Unclip the plug to gain better access.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_07.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('6828447c-8e47-4137-a347-313189b15378','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,8,8,'Splice CAN Bus Harness','Take the supplied CAN Bus harness and using the connectors splice into the vehicle harness as indicated below:
WHITE into BLACK vehicle wire
BLUE into WHITE vehicle wire','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_08.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('97927d3f-e578-488c-82b2-0ca085368a32','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,9,9,'Connect to CAN Bus Harness','Take the wire from step 7 and connect to the canbus harness as indicated below:
WHITE into Switch Positive
BLACK into Switch Negative','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_09.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('17596e09-134e-4948-ac89-ef349afca207','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,10,10,'Connect T-Patch to OBD Port','Using the supplied T-Patch, connect the red fused wire to the back of Pin 16 on the OBD port.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_10.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('0a439774-343c-4132-ab5a-d7cdd9e3e11d','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,11,11,'Install OEM Style Switch','Remove the blank from the desired location and plug in & fit the supplied OEM style switch.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/pdf-extracts/315e05d8-f036-4e58-864a-ca8b3bd0bbbd/step_11.jpeg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
('4692dc54-8404-42f8-afba-13b94e2329bc','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,12,12,'Attach Earth Wire and Refit Panels','Attach black earth wire to any available earth point. Refit all interior panels.
NOTE: Ensure all wiring is carefully routed, tucked out of the way and cable-tied in place to avoid wires conflicting with vehicle operations.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/guide-images/steps/0cb2c30c-7098-49e6-bd72-2d84d961e861.png','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/guide-images/steps/0cb2c30c-7098-49e6-bd72-2d84d961e861.png',NULL,NULL,NULL),
('01c5b786-6d97-4495-9c88-f5c0f6f674ba','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,13,13,'Reconnect Battery and Test','Reattach the negative terminal to the battery. Install the ring terminals to the positive and negative battery terminals as indicated by colour. Test the light bar.
NOTE: The RAV4 can have variations in the factory wiring loom, which may result in no high beam signal outputting to the light bar. Contact us if this occurs.','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/guide-images/steps/1be818ef-a42a-4f12-82da-4eb98f1cf833.png','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/guide-images/steps/1be818ef-a42a-4f12-82da-4eb98f1cf833.png',NULL,NULL,NULL),
('b54c3046-dd87-4de2-adfa-9ca37cac0cca','62eebb1e-9646-460a-af02-c7a5d0832eae',NULL,14,14,'High Beam Pickup Wiring Diagram','','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/guide-images/steps/3b5a9e4a-0e80-418c-b775-81ef2b421cc6.png','https://dwzvpraankfpaswjkpdc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/guide-images/steps/3b5a9e4a-0e80-418c-b775-81ef2b421cc6.png',NULL,NULL,NULL)
